Description: Body sherd (mended from three fragments) of Attic presumably black-figured pottery cup, possibly a Siana cup; in tondo, part of undetermined motif; around, three rows of staggered dots between two sets of triple dilute lines; alternating added red and black tongues; exterior: glazed black with reserved band.
Curator's comments: There is no evidence of black figure related incision on the sherd.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0387) (Phase 1)
